  "body": "# Problem\n\nI have to send multiple transactions all at once and type in my password again and again and again\n\n## Implementation\n\nI dont know if it is possible (or practical), but i would love a feature that would allow me to temporarily unlock my key and send a bunch of txs without having to type in the pw every time...\n\nIn my dream situation, i could choose a number of txs AND an amount of time (max 30 minutes) that i could send txs freely from my phone without having to type in the password... \n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe PR that does this i dont expect to ever happen, i would expect the keys being exposed locally is just something that never happens... and that this would open up some other dangerous exploits... but its worth saying hello and I Love Status...\n\n## Notes\n\nI only am submitting this because it crossed my mind to change the pw to be shorter just so i could have an easier time to send multiple txs... but thats not as good as this workaround... and if i make it a simple pw... i might be lazy and leave it there... \n\n## Future Steps\n\nThank you guys again for building such a great wallet. I love it and use it a lot for onboarding people... and thats why I would want this feature, so i could on board many people at once at a meet up... \n\nThank you guys for pushing so hard towards our decentralized future ;-D\n\nMuch love,\nGriff",
